    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-10-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr
                                Campbell</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-10-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 5, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Mr. Haldeman’s despatch No. 56 has been
                            received.</p>
                <p>The appointment which it announces of Baron N. de Wetterstedt as envoy
                            extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary to Washington is duly
                            appreciated as a mark of the friendly regard of the King of Sweden
                            towards the United States.</p>
                <p>You will please assure Count Manderstrom that the Baron de Wetterstedt
                            will be cordially welcomed in this country as the representative from
                            his Swedish Majesty.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James H. Campbell</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., <hi rend="italic">Stockholm.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
